Good:
+ The dealer, a great NPC and largely responsible why you will want to continue the game;
+ That feel, where a game is a life or death affair, something more than just a game;
+ Replay factor, plenty of cards to collect.


This game is not a card game as such, it uses the universe" of cards (regular

I'm going out of my way of not really bothering about reviewing games just to say this:

-  If you don't like  any the multiple sub-genres involved in this game (deck-building, RPG, old-school tabletop, Rogue-like, Arkhan-like combat) just don't bother giving bad reviews, you won't get the message the game is trying to deliver (it could change your mind on those, hardly though);

-  If you're new to  those genres, buy it and play with an open mind, don't give quick judgment and the game will show its beauty to you (don't just give up after a few plays);

-  If you , like myself,  enjoy  most to all of the aspects of those genres, buy and play it, you'll surprise yourself with a richly complex and mysterious story inside this very much balanced (don't let the bad reviews get in your head) tabletop inspired (some luck involved, sometimes, and  not  unfair) and build your own adventure RPG. The combat element is tough, but satisfactory and rewarding, it's not 100% as perfect as some AAA titles but it does a good job and that's enough to have a good experience with the combat part. This is an indie game, so don't expect a perfectly polished game in all aspects, the Devs (who are such great guys and responsive towards the community) are constantly polishing and releasing patches (and DLCs) to fix and improve the game experience, so it just gets better and better.

TL:DR version

- Don't like the genres? Don't bother (but it would be nice of you if you bought it to help the indie community C: );

- Aren't familiarized with the genres? Try it for yourself (truly do, you won't regret it) and don't let bad reviews get to you;

-Like those genres?  YOU WILL ♥♥♥♥ING LOVE THIS PIECE OF ART CALLED
HAND OF FATE.


(sorry if my english is not 100%, spent too much time without contact with it and it's a little rusty  ^u^').

Early Access Review

I really enjoy the collecting of a card game with the fights of an RPG and the toughness of a roguelike, first i thought 20€ may be mutch, but they are worth it. A few features are still missing, but i hope they will be added soon.

@They potential buyer: If you like roguelikes,cardgames and RPGs give them your 20€
@Devs: Keep up your good work and you will get more of these babys from me €€€€
